Rehabilitation Research Institute of Singapore invites applications for the position of Project Officer.
Key Responsibilities:

  Design and develop a robotic actuation system, including exploration of novel actuation technologies
  Design and develop the controllers, including simulations and embedded system programming

Job Requirements:

  Bachelor degree in Mechatronics, Electrical &amp; Electronic Engineering, Computer Engineering or other related majors
  Understanding of control theories and familiar with actuators and embedded system
  Experience in robotics is advantageous
  Possess good communication skills, sense of responsibility and ability to work independently

We regret that only shortlisted candidates will be notified.